WEBVTT

00:09.120 --> 00:10.640
And then they'll kill you.

00:11.760 --> 00:13.320
You're dead, anyway.

00:16.160 --> 00:17.400
For fuck's sake....

00:18.680 --> 00:20.400
For fuck's sake, man.

00:21.400 --> 00:22.520
Come on, man.

00:30.080 --> 00:31.480
-On your knees.
-No.

00:33.080 --> 00:34.280
Please, don't kill me.

00:34.520 --> 00:37.200
SATURDAY
12:30 PM

00:38.160 --> 00:39.320
Don't look at me.

00:42.000 --> 00:42.880
Don't look at me.

00:43.480 --> 00:45.320
-Please, don't.
-Don't fucking look at me.

00:45.400 --> 00:47.120
Don't fucking look at me.

01:02.400 --> 01:03.600
What the hell was that?

01:03.760 --> 01:06.120
26 HOURS OF ROBBERY

01:06.200 --> 01:07.320
What happened?

01:07.400 --> 01:08.680
Calm down, Jesus!

01:08.760 --> 01:11.040
Calm down. Have some fucking strength,

01:11.120 --> 01:14.720
or we won't get out alive, right?
You have to give it some balls.

01:34.920 --> 01:35.880
Thanks.

01:36.200 --> 01:37.400
Shut up, shut up.

01:37.480 --> 01:38.360
-Thanks.
-Shut up.

01:38.720 --> 01:41.680
Thanks. Tell them you killed me
and you got rid of the body.

01:41.760 --> 01:43.640
-I'll hide.
-Where the fuck will you hide?

01:43.800 --> 01:44.920
In vault 2.

01:45.320 --> 01:48.440
I've got the fingerprint. Nobody will get
in. I'll hide. Tell them you killed me.

01:48.600 --> 01:51.120
-Tell them.
-There's not a single drop of blood.

01:51.280 --> 01:54.000
-There's not a single drop of blood.
-Shoot me here, come on.

01:54.080 --> 01:55.920
-Shoot me in the hand.
-Don't talk nonsense.

01:56.000 --> 01:57.600
-Shoot me.
-For fuck's sake!

01:57.680 --> 01:58.680
-In my shoulder.
-The shoulder?

01:58.760 --> 01:59.760
Shoot me in the shoulder.

01:59.840 --> 02:02.520
The shoulder is so close to the lung.
I can't do it.

02:02.840 --> 02:05.040
In my thigh, it bleeds a lot.
I've seen it.

02:05.120 --> 02:08.280
My brother got hurt with an iron
and he bled a lot. Come on. Come.

02:11.960 --> 02:13.480
Bite my hand if you want.

02:30.000 --> 02:31.800
Okay, okay.

02:32.400 --> 02:33.360
Okay.

02:33.440 --> 02:36.080
-Okay, okay.
-No!

03:03.800 --> 03:05.120
Two shots...

03:07.120 --> 03:10.560
Have you got bad aim
or do blondes get you nervous?

03:11.400 --> 03:13.760
If she grabs your knee
and begs you not to kill her,

03:13.840 --> 03:14.720
it's not easy.

03:16.640 --> 03:18.040
Why didn't you kill her?

03:21.400 --> 03:22.960
You're a fucking bastard.

03:23.200 --> 03:26.080
You don't want to stain your hands
with blood, but you stain mine.

03:27.360 --> 03:30.120
If you ever touch me again, you're dead.

03:33.960 --> 03:37.960
There's a coal boiler in the basement.
Put her inside.

03:40.520 --> 03:43.240
Later you'll clean all this.

05:14.480 --> 05:15.440
Paula?

05:17.320 --> 05:19.520
Paula, honey! Where are you?

05:19.680 --> 05:21.400
Where are you, Paula?

05:22.080 --> 05:23.400
Paula, honey!

05:25.320 --> 05:26.360
Paula...

05:32.080 --> 05:34.440
"Now I don't live in Almazán.
I live in Madrid.

05:35.360 --> 05:38.440
The bus that goes downtown is number 21.

05:39.480 --> 05:42.080
I've got two daughters.
The keys are in a drawer in the hall.

05:42.240 --> 05:44.400
I live with Raquel and Paula.
My brother is sick.

05:44.560 --> 05:47.000
The keys are...
I've got two daughters. Raquel is...

05:47.160 --> 05:48.760
Paula always has her way.

05:48.920 --> 05:51.600
Paula's father
has got a restraining order.

05:52.120 --> 05:55.120
Never let Paula go with her father."

06:16.080 --> 06:17.040
Hello?

06:17.920 --> 06:21.240
Professor, the one hour term
I gave you has finished.

06:21.800 --> 06:23.680
I need to know
if you're going to surrender.

06:24.640 --> 06:27.240
When you were a child,
what games did you play in the playground?

06:31.960 --> 06:33.680
With... the jump rope,

06:34.320 --> 06:36.680
"hitting the can, the donkey...."

06:38.400 --> 06:40.840
I played ladybirds too.
I was very good at that.

06:41.120 --> 06:42.880
"I played cops and robbers."

06:43.360 --> 06:44.240
Is it familiar?

06:44.640 --> 06:47.000
Some of us played cops
and had to catch the others

06:47.080 --> 06:50.560
and when they got you, they got you,
but I don't remember a single child

06:50.640 --> 06:54.520
in that playground who surrendered
before he was caught.

06:55.160 --> 06:58.760
Children in the school playground
do not risk going to prison

06:58.840 --> 07:00.080
for 8 or 16 years.

07:00.680 --> 07:03.200
You're right. You're absolutely right.

07:03.280 --> 07:05.440
That's why I asked my mates.

07:06.160 --> 07:07.600
"We voted, and you know what?"

07:09.200 --> 07:10.520
We're enthusiasts.

07:10.600 --> 07:13.560
Finally we've decided
to go for the zero years in prison.

07:19.680 --> 07:22.200
"Hello, it's Raquel.
I can't answer right now.

07:22.280 --> 07:24.920
If it's something urgent,
leave a message after the beep."

07:26.320 --> 07:29.240
A lot of people are suffering.
What do you plan to do?

07:29.720 --> 07:31.080
Take paper and a pen.

07:32.880 --> 07:34.120
"I need a lorry"

07:34.280 --> 07:36.840
a 3-axle one,
with a trailer for 18 tonnes,

07:36.920 --> 07:40.000
two more tankers,
with propane gas to escort it

07:40.080 --> 07:43.000
and the ship Malaika with flag
from Saint Vincent and the Grenadines.

07:43.080 --> 07:45.680
Is it familiar?
It's the one seized nine months ago

07:45.760 --> 07:47.440
with 2,800 kilos of cocaine.

07:47.520 --> 07:49.560
It's docked at Ferrol's military port.

07:49.920 --> 07:52.560
It'll won't be easy to get
the green light to your requests,

07:53.240 --> 07:56.280
due to... logistic issues,
safety issues....

07:57.600 --> 07:58.840
Imagine this:

08:00.320 --> 08:05.080
a building collapses
and there are 67 people inside.

08:06.920 --> 08:09.480
How many arrangements do you think
they would approve to save

08:09.560 --> 08:12.840
the lives of those innocent people?
Inspector, let's be clear.

08:13.680 --> 08:17.800
You only have two choices.
One: to punish us. Two: to save lives.

08:17.880 --> 08:19.960
And I'm afraid
you can't choose both things.

08:21.000 --> 08:22.960
"You have a new message.

08:23.040 --> 08:24.840
Mum, I've just finished. I'm on my way.

08:25.320 --> 08:27.680
To call back, press 1."

08:30.240 --> 08:31.720
I'm going to promise you one thing.

08:37.960 --> 08:39.160
If you refuse to punish us,

08:39.240 --> 08:42.320
I'll give you those 67 hostages
in perfect health,

08:42.400 --> 08:44.240
when we are in international waters.

08:44.320 --> 08:46.440
And I assure that's not
the first choice I had.

08:46.520 --> 08:49.000
I hate the sea, the fish
and the sand on the beach.

08:50.080 --> 08:52.760
"But life don't always give you
an easy way out, don't you think?"

08:59.280 --> 09:02.680
"I got a message from my daughter
this morning, from that phone.

09:02.760 --> 09:07.400
I don't... I'm Raquel Murillo's mother.
And I can't locate her.

09:07.680 --> 09:10.600
Please, do you know where she is?
It's urgent."

09:14.120 --> 09:16.800
We're bringing that lorry
to get them out of that mouse trap.

09:16.880 --> 09:18.720
It'll be easier for us in the open field.

09:19.240 --> 09:21.400
Let's get the vehicles ready
with narcotic gas.

09:21.480 --> 09:23.840
-They're not coming out.
-How do you know?

09:24.080 --> 09:27.080
They opened that vault,
but they didn't want the money.

09:28.480 --> 09:30.000
They waited for the police.

09:32.200 --> 09:33.080
They shot.

09:34.080 --> 09:36.200
"They dropped two bags,
coincidentally open,

09:36.280 --> 09:38.520
dispersing the notes in the street."

09:40.080 --> 09:42.040
-So?
-They wanted to pretend they were trapped

09:42.120 --> 09:43.960
to win two days of negotiation.

09:44.120 --> 09:45.880
But they're inside on purpose.

09:45.960 --> 09:49.320
With a Browning machine gun,
red overalls, masks and everything.

09:51.600 --> 09:54.400
They triggered the alarm
two hours after they had come in.

09:54.560 --> 09:56.520
"Once they had opened the safe vault."

09:56.600 --> 09:59.960
They used the money as the excuse for
a common robbery, but it wasn't casual.

10:00.040 --> 10:02.120
They came in
when the ambassador's daughter was there.

10:02.200 --> 10:04.000
"That's why that man
speaks without hesitation.

10:04.160 --> 10:06.640
He's in control, because he knows
everything goes according to plan.

10:07.240 --> 10:10.360
What plan is better than going out
with the eight millions of the safe vault?

10:13.920 --> 10:16.160
They're printing their own unmarked money.

10:20.920 --> 10:23.160
-It's here, right?
-Yes, wait.

10:23.240 --> 10:24.360
Be careful.

10:29.960 --> 10:32.360
-Why isn't it working?
-The finger isn't clean.

10:33.040 --> 10:34.840
Has it got delayed opening,
like the other one?

10:34.920 --> 10:35.800
No.

10:41.120 --> 10:42.640
-Okay.
-Come on.

11:09.000 --> 11:10.880
-You can't come in.
-I've got a phone call

11:10.960 --> 11:12.760
for inspector Murillo, Raquel Murillo.

11:13.360 --> 11:15.680
-Fine.
-It's urgent and private.

11:17.640 --> 11:19.880
-It's urgent.
-Go ahead.

11:22.520 --> 11:24.360
-Thanks.
-Stretch your arms.

11:33.320 --> 11:34.680
Come with me.

11:38.560 --> 11:41.920
-An incoming call in the repeater.
-Record it. Now.

11:43.480 --> 11:44.560
It's recording.

11:44.640 --> 11:46.960
"A civilian is going towards
the command post, he's with Almansa.

11:47.120 --> 11:49.680
He wants to see the inspector,
a private and urgent matter."

11:52.240 --> 11:55.680
Excuse me, inspector, but I've got
your mother on the phone.

11:56.240 --> 11:59.000
I guess you phoned her from my phone.
Excuse me.

11:59.600 --> 12:01.800
I think it has to do with your daughter.

12:15.960 --> 12:17.480
-Hello?
-"Darling."

12:17.640 --> 12:19.120
-Mum, what's up?
-Stop recording.

12:19.200 --> 12:21.040
-"Paula has left with her father."
-What?

12:21.120 --> 12:23.720
-"He told me it'd only be a while."
-Mum, what did you do?

12:23.800 --> 12:26.680
-"They haven't come back yet."
-Alberto has got a restraining order.

12:26.760 --> 12:29.760
He can only see Paula every 15 days
and he can't get in the house.

12:29.920 --> 12:31.800
-"I know, darling."
-Stop recording, jeez!

12:32.080 --> 12:33.920
-We can't.
-Then turn down the volume!

12:34.000 --> 12:34.920
"I couldn't..."

12:35.520 --> 12:36.640
Mum, mum.

12:36.720 --> 12:39.040
-How long ago did they leave?
-"Two hours, I think."

12:39.120 --> 12:40.880
Okay, wait for me there.

12:52.440 --> 12:57.400
-What a mess have you got here, huh?
-Almansa, take him out, please.

13:08.440 --> 13:12.440
The shots you heard were caused
by a situation with the police.

13:14.000 --> 13:17.600
It was caused by a hostage
who didn't follow my rules

13:18.240 --> 13:20.440
and tried to contact...

13:21.240 --> 13:22.680
using this phone.

13:39.880 --> 13:41.200
And I wonder...

13:42.600 --> 13:46.040
If I have Miss Gaztambide's phone...

13:47.720 --> 13:49.240
Whose is this one?

13:51.600 --> 13:53.560
Is this tune familiar to any of you?

13:59.080 --> 14:00.120
What has happened?

14:01.000 --> 14:02.080
What are you doing?

14:02.760 --> 14:04.120
We've all heard the shots.

14:04.400 --> 14:06.160
I've asked you what the hell has happened.

14:07.160 --> 14:08.040
Not here.

14:10.000 --> 14:11.320
We said no victims.

14:11.640 --> 14:14.040
She had a phone. What should
I have done, give her some lashes?

14:14.120 --> 14:17.080
Scare her, not kill her.
Cut her an ear, like in the movies.

14:17.160 --> 14:20.160
If she had given information to the police
about how many and where we are,

14:20.240 --> 14:22.240
now you'd be the one having been shot.

14:23.200 --> 14:24.640
But you'd keep your ear.

14:25.560 --> 14:26.560
Who shot?

14:28.040 --> 14:28.960
Denver.

14:30.880 --> 14:32.400
Too much hot blood.

14:33.200 --> 14:35.720
The Professor said
we wouldn't spill blood,

14:35.800 --> 14:38.320
-those were the rules.
-Well, there has just been a change

14:38.840 --> 14:40.640
concerning hostage control.

14:42.440 --> 14:43.360
Understood?

14:44.600 --> 14:48.320
Calm down, the public opinion is on
our side and that's not going to change.

14:48.400 --> 14:51.400
When they notice there's
a hostage missing, we won't be here.

14:52.080 --> 14:53.080
We'll be far away.

14:53.240 --> 14:54.920
Does the Professor know that? Huh?

14:55.600 --> 14:58.200
Does the Professor know you've broken
the first fucking rule of the plan?

14:58.360 --> 14:59.880
Are you telling me about the rules?

15:00.760 --> 15:04.880
You, who due to your affair
with this jerk almost killed an officer?

15:05.240 --> 15:07.280
We must call the Professor and tell him.

15:08.640 --> 15:09.640
Boy.

15:17.160 --> 15:18.440
Call him, Rio.

15:30.840 --> 15:31.920
He doesn't answer.

15:39.960 --> 15:42.800
You can't look out and control everything
24 hours a day.

15:42.880 --> 15:46.360
You must eat, sleep, go to the toilet.

15:46.440 --> 15:48.440
That's why I'm in charge here.

15:49.360 --> 15:51.760
We'll only get out of here
if we're professional.

15:51.960 --> 15:54.160
Can you tell me
what the heck is going on here?

15:54.640 --> 15:56.160
I could hear you from the outside.

15:57.480 --> 15:59.440
Berlin has ordered
the execution of a hostage.

16:06.360 --> 16:07.560
Who did it?

16:14.640 --> 16:15.720
Your son.

16:22.680 --> 16:26.560
"A thief is, by definition,
an inveterate optimist.

16:28.080 --> 16:30.000
They always think
everything will be all right,

16:31.280 --> 16:33.480
but the first who realised was Moscow.

16:39.360 --> 16:41.400
He was one of those men who are honest,

16:41.480 --> 16:45.440
who give confidence, take care of you
and tell bad jokes.

16:46.240 --> 16:47.640
I felt tenderness towards him."

16:51.400 --> 16:52.920
What are you listening to?

16:55.440 --> 16:56.320
Great music.

16:57.600 --> 16:59.720
Do you know how music was invented?

17:01.840 --> 17:03.960
-No.
-On a train.

17:05.320 --> 17:08.640
There was a father and his son,
whose name was Patxi.

17:09.040 --> 17:11.280
The boy was very worried
to know if the train

17:11.360 --> 17:14.360
would stop at their village or not.
Besides, the child was a real pest.

17:14.520 --> 17:16.840
And he kept on saying:
"Will it stop, dad?"

17:16.920 --> 17:20.160
And his father: "It will, Patxi."
"Will it stop, dad?" "It will, Patxi."

17:26.400 --> 17:30.280
And what about Denver and you?
Relatives and artistic duo in robberies?

17:32.800 --> 17:36.120
Yes, just like the Sacapuntas Duo,
but with burglaries.

17:37.080 --> 17:40.200
"That afternoon Moscow told me
how he had dragged his son

17:40.280 --> 17:42.080
to that crazy robbery."

17:42.800 --> 17:46.560
My son shouldn't be here.
But when the Professor

17:46.640 --> 17:49.840
told me about the plan,
I dragged him with me.

17:58.400 --> 17:59.280
Hey!

18:06.160 --> 18:07.040
There.

18:08.600 --> 18:09.920
Give me a hug, jeez.

18:13.240 --> 18:16.040
You really like the food in prison, right?

18:16.120 --> 18:20.000
-Don't touch me, they're gases.
-Gases, sure.

18:20.360 --> 18:22.520
And the saturated fats
they give us to eat there.

18:22.600 --> 18:24.200
-Right.
-Give me a cigarette, come on.

18:24.280 --> 18:25.960
I've got it ready. Here.

18:28.160 --> 18:30.120
How are you? How's your life?

18:30.200 --> 18:31.760
Fine. Here I am.

18:38.040 --> 18:40.400
-What's the matter?
-What do you mean?

18:40.800 --> 18:43.320
-I'm excited to see you, dad.
-Don't try to fool me.

18:43.880 --> 18:47.080
It's the sixth time you come to pick me up
and you've never looked that way.

18:47.480 --> 18:48.520
What the fuck is up?

18:52.200 --> 18:53.280
I've fucked it up.

18:55.000 --> 18:56.200
What the hell did you do?

18:57.600 --> 18:59.720
He had lost 800 pills.

19:00.120 --> 19:03.800
Of someone called Pole,
a shitty dealer from Alcorcón.

19:05.160 --> 19:07.280
It seems they had been stolen
from his car.

19:07.840 --> 19:08.840
And he's got a boss.

19:10.040 --> 19:11.440
That motherfucker is a lunatic.

19:12.680 --> 19:18.080
And they break your nasal septum,
they break you a leg...

19:19.000 --> 19:21.560
So everybody knows
you stole the drugs to the wrong man.

19:25.680 --> 19:30.240
Dad, the deadline is finishing
and I haven't got the dough.

19:30.400 --> 19:33.200
I swear to God I haven't got it,
they stole it from my car,

19:33.280 --> 19:36.600
I didn't sell it or anything. I didn't
take those pills, drugs make me ill.

19:44.440 --> 19:47.760
So, not to have his meniscus broken
by a baseball bat, you said:

19:48.880 --> 19:50.480
"Let's make him print notes."

19:50.560 --> 19:52.800
He's already done all the bad works:

19:54.280 --> 19:57.480
fur shops, savings banks, vans...

19:58.320 --> 20:01.400
And now... turn for a big one.

20:02.240 --> 20:05.120
If everything goes well,
I'm taking my son to a country

20:05.680 --> 20:08.000
whose name we can't even pronounce.

20:08.080 --> 20:11.320
Without Poles, without pending cases,
to start from scratch.

20:11.480 --> 20:14.880
But of course, with mojitos and beaches.

20:16.520 --> 20:18.520
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

20:18.680 --> 20:22.840
-Boy, don't you see I'm washing the floor?
-I left my notes to study.

20:23.320 --> 20:27.240
-You left your notes... Come on, beat it.
-Don't be a pest, let me do it.

20:28.040 --> 20:30.400
-Will you...?
-Dad, I have to study,

20:30.480 --> 20:33.840
-I left my notes. I'm coming.
-Beat it, come on. Come on.

20:34.600 --> 20:37.280
Come on, go away. Jeez.

20:41.760 --> 20:42.640
Moscow!

20:45.680 --> 20:46.720
Stop.

20:49.480 --> 20:52.520
For the last time,
go back to your position.

21:00.720 --> 21:01.960
What are you going to do?

21:02.800 --> 21:03.760
Shoot me?

21:05.800 --> 21:07.200
And then who?

21:07.960 --> 21:08.960
Everyone?

21:10.240 --> 21:12.160
Are you staying alone in this mouse trap?

21:41.760 --> 21:42.720
Son.

21:48.400 --> 21:49.880
Have you killed that woman?

22:02.080 --> 22:03.080
Dad.

22:10.120 --> 22:11.000
Nothing.

22:12.240 --> 22:13.560
-I can't breathe.
-Dad.

22:13.880 --> 22:16.120
Dad, what's up? What's up?

22:16.200 --> 22:17.880
Dad, is it a heart attack?

22:17.960 --> 22:21.120
Are you having a heart attack?
Dad, no, no.

22:21.200 --> 22:24.360
It's an anxiety attack.
Lie him down. Lie him down.

22:24.600 --> 22:26.960
-Dad, dad.
-That's it.

22:27.360 --> 22:31.160
"Lying on that floor full of blood,
Moscow knew there'd be no caipirinhas

22:31.880 --> 22:34.040
or any country they couldn't pronounce.

22:35.480 --> 22:38.240
He hadn't taken Denver there
to save him from something,

22:38.560 --> 22:41.480
but to sink him in a hole
from which he'd only get out arrested

22:42.040 --> 22:43.480
or with a bullet in his chest."

22:48.160 --> 22:49.880
Excuse me. Sorry.

22:51.200 --> 22:54.240
The shot we've heard before...
Is anyone hurt?

22:54.600 --> 22:56.200
Calm down, all right?

22:56.600 --> 22:58.640
Nobody was hurt. Okay?

22:59.080 --> 23:02.040
We only shot to dissuade
an intervention. Just that.

23:04.040 --> 23:06.920
You've heard that.
Stop thinking weird things

23:07.000 --> 23:10.360
about those shots, okay?
These people are robbers,

23:10.440 --> 23:13.000
not from the jihad or anything similar.

23:18.600 --> 23:21.320
-Mum.
-Honey, I'm sorry.

23:26.800 --> 23:28.360
It's a rollercoaster.

23:28.440 --> 23:30.640
Well, which is the other one,
where you get wet?

23:30.720 --> 23:33.040
-The spinning boats.
-Oh, yes, the boats.

23:36.080 --> 23:37.040
Your mother.

23:37.560 --> 23:42.080
Mummy! We've been
at the amusement park. It's so cool.

23:42.400 --> 23:43.480
Of course, honey.

23:44.880 --> 23:48.840
Mum, can you go upstairs
and leave the teddy bear in her room?

23:49.440 --> 23:50.400
Sure, honey.

23:52.800 --> 23:54.080
